content.description: Start on shelf above start hold for Annisette Cookies on parallel crack. Move left onto a juggy shelf. Follow the crack all the way left to a shelf by the tree, just above the finish for Annisette Cookies.
content.location: It is just above Annisette Cookies.

content.description: Start on a low crimp rail at the far left side of the face (just below obvious large crack). Move upwards on slots and cracks to top out on a ledge to the left of the cragâ€™s highest point.
content.location: It is as far left on the face as you can go.

content.description: Start on ledge at the far right by an obvious break in the wall (just left of Vulture Rock) along lowest, consistently horizontal crack. Stay on or below an obvious, lower, parallel crack as you traverse to the left. Finish on a juggy shelf by a tree on the left side of the wall.Avoid using detached rocks to the right for your feet.
content.location: Start at the far right of the face, traversing the lower of two obvious, parallel cracks.

content.description: Swamp Face West has a 25 foot tall, vertical face, not even 200 meters off the trail. It is the largest face of this section of woods. There is potential for easy, intermediate, and perhaps hard elimination problems.
